{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"430f70d8-1458-4424-b8c3-a1cfb84837d2","content":"The working directory is empty — there's no repository or template files here to inspect. \n\nHowever, I can answer based on the well-known .NET `dotnet new` templates:\n\n## `webapi` vs `webapp` — Parameter Comparison\n\n| Feature | **webapi** | **webapp** |\n|---------|-----------|-----------|\n| **Auth (`--auth`)** | ✅ Yes (None, Individual, IndividualB2C, SingleOrg, Windows) | ✅ Yes (None, Individual, IndividualB2C, SingleOrg, Windows) |\n| **AOT (`--aot`)** | ✅ Yes (since .NET 8) | ❌ No |\n| **Framework** | `--framework` | `--framework` |\n| **Use controllers** | `--use-controllers` | N/A |\n| **Minimal APIs** | Default (minimal) | N/A (Razor Pages) |\n| **HTTPS** | `--no-https` | `--no-https` |\n| **OpenAPI** | `--no-openapi` | N/A |\n| **Use Program.Main** | `--use-program-main` | `--use-program-main` |\n\n### Key Differences\n\n- **Authentication**: Both support it via `--auth`.\n- **AOT**: Only **`webapi`** supports `--aot` (Native AOT). The `webapp` template uses Razor Pages which are incompatible with AOT compilation.\n- **webapi** is for HTTP API services; **webapp** is for server-rendered Razor Pages UI.\n\nTo see the full parameter list yourself, run:\n```\ndotnet new webapi --help\ndotnet new webapp --help\n```\n\nWould you like me to install the .NET SDK and run those commands for live output?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"54e95847-69c1-4377-8be2-a17449da2ff6","outputTokens":424,"requestId":"6021:2A083D:69A70E8:7366C9A:69F9F96B"},"id":"7df64aa1-63f2-44d7-b76e-7c0b50ce0973","timestamp":"2026-05-05T14:06:48.121Z","parentId":"ce2fcffb-b7ba-4cb5-9f11-aa7c6ab23700"}
